properties.Title: Wind Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Wind gusts near 90 km/h are expected early this evening in Paulatuk and Sachs Harbour. These extreme winds will diminish before midnight but strong gusty winds are forecast to continue into Monday evening. ### Loose objects may be tossed by the wind and cause injury or damage. Wind warnings are issued when there is a significant risk of damaging winds. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NTstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NTStorm.

properties.Title: Snowfall Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: A low pressure system in northern Montana will track through southern Saskatchewan today. Periods of snow this morning will intensify by noon before tapering off this evening from the west to east as the low moves into northern Manitoba. Total snowfall accumulations to our warned areas is expected to be 10 to 15 centimeters. ### There may be a significant impact on rush hour traffic in urban areas. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to SKstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #SKStorm.

properties.Title: Update: High Water Advisory Alert Continued For The Red River Between Emerson And The Red River Floodway Inlet Control Structure
properties.Summary:
Description: Update: This is a Manitoba Emergency Alert. Manitoba Infrastructure's Hydrologic Forecast Centre has issued a High Water Advisory for the Red River between Emerson and the Red River Floodway Inlet Control Structure due to expected high flows. If you are in the affected area, be watchful of local waterways as flooding is likely to occur. Do not attempt to cross fast flowing waters of unknown depth. Avoid flooded areas. Follow all directions by the local authorities. Listen for updates and take all necessary precautions to stay safe. Up-to-date information is available at www.gov.mb.ca/flooding and www.manitoba511.ca or stay tuned to local media.
Expires: 2020-04-06T12:00:00-05:00

properties.Title: Snowfall Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Snowfall with total amounts of 10 to 15 cm is expected. A low in northern Montana tracking northeastwards through Saskatchewan today will arrive in central Manitoba this evening. Heavy snow will begin in western regions later this afternoon and spread northeastwards throughout the night. Snow will then taper off from the southwest as the system moves continues to move northeastwards on Tuesday. The system is expected to weaken slightly on Tuesday but warnings may need to be expanded further to the northeast as the system evolves. Total snowfall accumulations of 10 to 15 cm are expected by Tuesday afternoon in the warned areas. ### Visibility may be suddenly reduced at times in heavy snow. Snowfall warnings are issued when significant snowfall is expected. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to MBstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #MBStorm.
Expires: 2020-04-07T01:21:31-00:00
